# ~/homelab-k8s-services/.gitmessage
#
# <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# --- COMMIT MESSAGE GUIDELINES ---
#
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature or service
#   fix      - Bug fixes
#   docs     - Documentation only changes
#   refactor - Code change that neither fixes bug nor adds feature
#   chore    - Changes to build process or auxiliary tools
#   platform - Platform/infrastructure services
#   app      - Application services
#   config   - Configuration changes
#   security - Security-related changes
#   ci       - CI/CD pipeline changes
#
# Scopes (examples):
#   platform   - cert-manager, ingress-nginx, metallb, monitoring
#   app        - gitea, vaultwarden, immich, open-webui
#   docs       - documentation changes
#   ci         - github actions, automation
#   helm       - helm chart related
#   kustomize  - kustomization changes
#
# Description:
#   - Use imperative mood ("add" not "added" or "adds")
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period at the end
#   - Max 50 characters
#
# Body:
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Explain what and why, not how
#   - Use bullet points with - or *
#
# Footer:
#   - Reference issues: "Closes #123" or "Fixes #456"
#   - Breaking changes: "BREAKING CHANGE: description"
#
# --- EXAMPLES ---
#
# feat(platform): add cert-manager with Let's Encrypt support
#
# feat(app): add gitea self-hosted git service
#
# - Configure PostgreSQL database
# - Add persistent volume for repositories
# - Include ingress with TLS termination
# - Add backup configuration
#
# Closes #15
#
# fix(platform): resolve metallb IP pool conflict
#
# docs(gitea): add deployment and troubleshooting guide
#
# chore: update kubernetes manifests to v1.29
#
# security(vaultwarden): add network policies and RBAC
#
# BREAKING CHANGE: change ingress class from nginx to ingress-nginx
